import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline

class KNN:
    def __init__(self, k=3):
        self.k = k

    def fit(self, X_train, y_train):
        self.X_train = X_train
        self.y_train = y_train

    def predict(self, X):
        # Calculate the Euclidean distances between X and all examples in the training set
        distances = np.linalg.norm(self.X_train[:, np.newaxis] - X, axis=2)
        # Get the indices of the k nearest neighbors
        k_indices = np.argsort(distances, axis=0)[:self.k]
        # Get the labels of the k nearest neighbors
        k_nearest_labels = self.y_train[k_indices]
        # Majority vote, most common class label
        y_pred = [Counter(labels).most_common(1)[0][0] for labels in k_nearest_labels.T]
        return np.array(y_pred)

# Train SVM model
svm_pca = SVC(kernel='linear')
svm_pca.fit(X_train_pca, y_train)

# Define custom color maps for better distinction
cmap_light = ListedColormap(['#FFDDDD', '#DDFFDD'])
cmap_bold = ListedColormap(['#FF0000', '#00FF00'])

# Plot decision boundary in 3D
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(11, 15))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')

# Scatter plot of training data
scatter = ax.scatter(
    X_train_pca[:, 0], 
    X_train_pca[:, 1], 
    X_train_pca[:, 2], 
    c=y_train, 
    edgecolor='k', 
    cmap=cmap_bold, 
    marker='o', 
    s=80,  # Larger size for better visibility
    alpha=0.8  # Slight transparency for better visibility
)

# Create a meshgrid for the decision boundary
xx, yy = np.meshgrid(np.linspace(X_train_pca[:, 0].min(), X_train_pca[:, 0].max(), 100),
                     np.linspace(X_train_pca[:, 1].min(), X_train_pca[:, 1].max(), 100))

# Predict decision boundary
zz = np.zeros(xx.shape)
for i in range(xx.shape[0]):
    for j in range(xx.shape[1]):
        zz[i, j] = -(svm_pca.coef_[0, 0] * xx[i, j] + svm_pca.coef_[0, 1] * yy[i, j] + svm_pca.intercept_[0]) / svm_pca.coef_[0, 2]

# Plot decision boundary surface
ax.plot_surface(xx, yy, zz, color='c', alpha=0.3)

# Customize plot
ax.set_title('SVM Decision Boundary with PCA', fontsize=18, weight='bold')
ax.set_xlabel('Principal Component 1', fontsize=16)
ax.set_ylabel('Principal Component 2', fontsize=16)
ax.set_zlabel('Principal Component 3', fontsize=16)

# Optionally add a legend for better clarity
handles = [
    plt.Line2D([0], [0], marker='o', color='w', markerfacecolor=cmap_bold(0), markersize=10, label='Class 0'),
    plt.Line2D([0], [0], marker='o', color='w', markerfacecolor=cmap_bold(1), markersize=10, label='Class 1')
]
ax.legend(handles=handles, fontsize=14)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Define a function to print and store metrics
def print_metrics(y_true, y_pred, y_proba):
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred)
    precision = precision_score(y_true, y_pred)
    recall = recall_score(y_true, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_true, y_pred)
    roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_true, y_proba)
    return accuracy, precision, recall, f1, roc_auc

# Collect metrics for each classifier
metrics = {
    'Logistic Regression': print_metrics(y_test, log_reg_pred, log_reg_proba),
    'SVM': print_metrics(y_test, svm_pred, svm_proba),
    'Random Forest': print_metrics(y_test, rf_pred, rf_proba)
}

# Display the metrics
metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics, index=['Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'F1-score', 'ROC-AUC'])
metrics_df

values1 = metrics_df['Logistic Regression']
values2 = metrics_df['SVM']
values3 = metrics_df['Random Forest']

fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Scatterpolar(
    r=values1,
    theta=categories,
    fill='toself',
    name='Logistic Regression',
    marker=dict(color='rgba(210, 105, 230, 0.8)')
), go.Scatterpolar(
    r=values2,
    theta=categories,
    fill='toself',
    name='SVM',
    marker=dict(color='rgba(100, 149, 237, 0.8)')
), go.Scatterpolar(

    theta=categories,
    fill='toself',
    name='Random Forest',
    marker=dict(color='rgba(144, 238, 144, 0.8)')
)])

        radialaxis=dict(

# Plot ROC curves for all classifiers together
plt.figure(figsize=(9, 9))
colors = ['blue', 'green', 'red']
classifiers = ['Logistic Regression', 'SVM', 'Random Forest']
probabilities = [log_reg_proba, svm_proba, rf_proba]

for name, proba, color in zip(classifiers, probabilities, colors):
    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, proba)
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'{name} (AUC = {roc_auc_score(y_test, proba):.2f})', color=color, lw=2)

plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--', lw=2)

plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate', fontsize=14)
